{
  "stem": "7157.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we would stuff the tobacco into this other half, with the paper, and kind of burn the end a little bit with a match and cut it off, so the tobacco wouldn't fall out.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, you know, when you do something for 10 hours a day, like George and I, we made hundreds of cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know, maybe even thousands.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not per day, but whatever.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then my mother was able to go out and sell these cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And everything my mother did-- again, because, going back to the woman, and my mother was a redhead, you know, so she blended right in to the Polish environment.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't like, she didn't, so to say, look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And obviously, with a woman they couldn't check if she was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she would go out and sell these cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's how we made, you know, some money to-- Make ends meet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--To support ourselves or to, to get food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But many times, you know, there was no tobacco, we couldn't make them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember my-- Wujek and I and George would go out in the fields and try to steal potatoes from farms, try to steal food.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many times we would, they would find out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we'd, again, have to move.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was a constant plight, you might say, moving, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One story I'd like to relate, which is a little off, off the path.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I've told this story to my kids so many times, they would be angry if I didn't tell it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But in all of this mess, we once went on an outing, you know, a Sunday outing, and, the four of us.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
